<item>
            <title>[HTTPCLIENT-17] need a way to set time out when using HttpClient and HttpMultiClient</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HTTPCLIENT-17</link>
                <project id="12310360" key="HTTPCLIENT">HttpComponents HttpClient</project>
                        <description>When using class HttpClient or HttpMultiClient, there is no way to set the time &lt;br/&gt;
out value. Because the setTimeout method is in HttpConnection and HttpClient or &lt;br/&gt;
HttpMultiClient doesn&amp;#39;t expose the HttpConnection object. One option is to add &lt;br/&gt;
a method setTimeout in HttpClient and HttpMultiClient. Another option is to add &lt;br/&gt;
such a method in HttpMethod.</description>
                <environment>Operating System: other&lt;br/&gt;
Platform: Other</environment>
