                    <comment id="12379231" author="jan.vissers@cumquat.nl" created="Tue, 2 Apr 2002 18:40:19 +0100"  >This is very, very strange. The nightly builds offer me a method to set &lt;br/&gt;
timeout on the HttpConnection object, however the &amp;quot;official&amp;quot; download doesn&amp;#39;t &lt;br/&gt;
have this functionality. It&amp;#39;s exactly this functionality I&amp;#39;m looking for, so a &lt;br/&gt;
quick fix would be highly appreciated.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Q. How safe is it to use the nightly build instead of the &amp;quot;official&amp;quot; download?</comment>
                    <comment id="12379232" author="marc.saegesser@apropos.com" created="Sun, 7 Apr 2002 22:37:04 +0100"  >The &amp;#39;official&amp;#39; download (2.0 alpha 1) is pretty old and there have been some &lt;br/&gt;
significant changes since then.  &lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
The nightly builds are fairly stable, but there are still some &amp;#39;hotspots&amp;#39; that &lt;br/&gt;
are still undergoing some change.  Specifically, the HttpMultiClient related &lt;br/&gt;
stuff.  Most of the changes in this area to complete missing functionality, but &lt;br/&gt;
there may be some changes to the API prior to the final release.</comment>
                    <comment id="12379233" author="rwaldhof@us.britannica.com" created="Mon, 29 Apr 2002 22:36:26 +0100"  >Fixed in nightly builds?</comment>
                    <comment id="12379234" author="karl.johan@klei.st" created="Fri, 10 May 2002 19:56:24 +0100"  >Jan, when you say &amp;quot;nightly builds offer me a method to set &lt;br/&gt;
timeout on the HttpConnection object&amp;quot;, do you mean HttpConnection.setSoTimeout() ?&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
But how to get hold of the HttpConnection from my HttpClient?&lt;br/&gt;
The connection field is private. Should I subclass HttpClient,&lt;br/&gt;
and create a getClient() method?&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
I&amp;#39;m tempered to re-open this bug, but since I&amp;#39;m a recent HttpClient user,&lt;br/&gt;
I remain calm...&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Please also note the related &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HTTPCLIENT-1&quot; title=&quot;Timeout value for a connection&quot;&gt;&lt;strike&gt;HTTPCLIENT-1&lt;/strike&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br/&gt;
</comment>
                    <comment id="12379235" author="karl.johan@klei.st" created="Sun, 12 May 2002 22:50:02 +0100"  >Sorry for the spam, but I&amp;#39;d like to correct myself:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;quot;Should I subclass HttpClient, and create a getConnection() method?&amp;quot;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;^^^^^^^^^^&lt;br/&gt;
</comment>
                    <comment id="12379236" author="karl.johan@klei.st" created="Sun, 12 May 2002 23:09:30 +0100"  >Nah... cannot subclass HttpClient, since &amp;quot;connection&amp;quot; is declared as private&lt;br/&gt;
(why not protected???)&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Rather I _copied_ HttpClient, and added this method:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
void setTimeout(int ms)&lt;br/&gt;
{&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;if ( connection == null )&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;{&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;return;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;}&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;try&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;{&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;connection.setSoTimeout(ms);&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;}&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;catch (SocketException ex) { ex.printStackTrace(); }&lt;br/&gt;
}&lt;br/&gt;
</comment>
